user.name: Sophie Snowball
snippet:
The worst experience ever. Not only for me the patient but for my family too. I was brought to this hospital by ambulance in an emergency. A previous surgery I had had, didn't work and I needed a new ventricle valve placed. What we were not informed if it the lady "Dr" brain surgeon who would do the operation was infact a resident. This to me is surprising as in most countries it is illegal not to inform the patient.

To top it off, 10 hours at the most after brain surgery I spent in ICU, which I was sent home from. My mum crying begging the Dr and nurses to keep me at least another night. They didn't pay attention to her concerns. So I reluctantly signed the paperwork and was sent home.

After this I had problems with the valve as it broke apart in my body. Causing me to have another steam of problems. The follow up care in this hospital is non existent. Absolutely disgusting how they treated both myself and my mum.

Go ANYWHERE ELSE!
